== RubyCocoa

During development I run the RubyCocoa edge code (at least r1983).

Get it:
$ svn co https://rubycocoa.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/rubycocoa/trunk/src rubycocoa

Build it (thread tests will fail! it needs a patched libruby):
$ cd rubycocoa
$ rake build

Optionally build Ruby-style Cocoa API reference (needs Hpricot & latest reference update (july 2007), Xcode.app -> Prefs -> Doc. -> Update):
$ rake doc

Install it:
$ sudo rake install

== Kari.app

Adjust CampKari.rb to your env. E.g. if you use a macports ruby:
  @camp_kari.launchPath = '/opt/local/bin/camping'
  ...
  @camp_kari.environment = { 'PATH' => '/opt/local/bin', 'HOME' => ENV['HOME'] }

Build/Run it:
$ rake run